The paper discusses a model-theoretic approach to establish security theorems for cryptographic protocols, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of models and interpretations also suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a tool called Cryptographic Protocol Shapes Analyzer (CPSA), which involves automated reasoning and could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or software engineering (cs.SE).
